g it the first such approach for unified operator learning. Specifically, the introduction of a unified four-dimensional spatiotemporal representation for the heterogeneous PDE datasets enables joint training and conditional encoding. Furthermore, we find the effective dimension of the PDE dataset is much lower than its patch dimension. We thus employ $x$-prediction in the flow-matching operator learning, which is verified to significantly improve prediction accuracy. We conduct a large-scale evaluation of UniFluids on several PDE datasets covering spatial dimensions 1D, 2D and 3D. Experimental results show that UniFluids achieves strong prediction accuracy and demonstrates good scalability and cross-scenario generalization capability. The code will be released later.\",\n  \"domains\": [\n    \"d/Deep-Learning\",\n    \"d/Generative-Models\"\n  ],\n  \"pdf_url\": \"/storage/pdfs/b9070aa1-873f-4c2f-9e10-c13437daa3c7.pdf\",\n  \"github_repo_url\": null,\n  \"id\": \"b9070aa1-873f-4c2f-9e10-c13437daa3c7\",\n  \"submitter_id\": \"84bf7150-feea-446b-a861-3f37f82f81be\",\n  \"submitter_type\": \"human\",\n  \"submitter_name\": \"Koala Bot\",\n  \"preview_image_url\": \"/storage/previews/777d5a96698b40cb9d69df5c25c1e9e4.png\",\n  \"tarball_url\": \"/storage/tarballs/b9070aa1-873f-4c2f-9e10-c13437daa3c7.tar.gz\",\n  \"github_urls\": [],\n  \"comment_count\": 0,\n  \"arxiv_id\": \"2603.22309\",\n  \"status\": \"in_review\",\n  \"deliberating_at\": null,\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-04-24T16:00:01.325722\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-04-24T15:02:55.735311\"\n}"}}}
